verses.text_plain: Behold, a king shall reign in righteousness, and princes shall rule in judgment.
verses.verse_html: 1Behold, a king shall reign in righteousness, and princes shall rule in judgment.

verses.text_plain: And a man shall be as an hiding place from the wind, and a covert from the tempest; as rivers of water in a dry place, as the shadow of a great rock in a weary land.
verses.verse_html:
2And a man shall be as an hiding place from the wind, and a covert from the tempest; as rivers of water in a dry place, as the shadow of a great rock in a weary land. ▼
▼ great: Heb. heavy

tokens.text: shall be as an hiding place

verses.text_plain: And the eyes of them that see shall not be dim, and the ears of them that hear shall hearken.
verses.verse_html: 3And the eyes of them that see shall not be dim, and the ears of them that hear shall hearken.

verses.text_plain: The heart also of the rash shall understand knowledge, and the tongue of the stammerers shall be ready to speak plainly.
verses.verse_html:
4The heart also of the rash shall understand knowledge, and the tongue of the stammerers shall be ready to speak plainly. ▼
▼ rash: Heb. hasty
 , ▼
▼ plainly: or, elegantly

verses.text_plain: The vile person shall be no more called liberal, nor the churl said to be bountiful.
verses.verse_html: 5The vile person shall be no more called liberal, nor the churl said to be bountiful.

verses.text_plain: For the vile person will speak villany, and his heart will work iniquity, to practise hypocrisy, and to utter error against the Lord, to make empty the soul of the hungry, and he will cause the drink of the thirsty to fail.
verses.verse_html: 6For the vile person will speak villany, and his heart will work iniquity, to practise hypocrisy, and to utter error against the Lord, to make empty the soul of the hungry, and he will cause the drink of the thirsty to fail.

tokens.text: and he will cause the drink

verses.text_plain: The instruments also of the churl are evil: he deviseth wicked devices to destroy the poor with lying words, even when the needy speaketh right.
verses.verse_html:
7The instruments also of the churl are evil: he deviseth wicked devices to destroy the poor with lying words, even when the needy speaketh right. ▼
▼ the needy…: or, he speaketh against the poor in judgment

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the needy…: or, he speaketh against the poor in judgment
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the needy…: or, he speaketh against the poor in judgment

verses.text_plain: But the liberal deviseth liberal things; and by liberal things shall he stand.
verses.verse_html:
8But the liberal deviseth liberal things; and by liberal things shall he stand. ▼
▼ stand: or, be established

footnotes.body_html: ▼ stand: or, be established

verses.text_plain: Rise up, ye women that are at ease; hear my voice, ye careless daughters; give ear unto my speech.
verses.verse_html: 9Rise up, ye women that are at ease; hear my voice, ye careless daughters; give ear unto my speech.

verses.text_plain: Many days and years shall ye be troubled, ye careless women: for the vintage shall fail, the gathering shall not come.
verses.verse_html:
10Many days and years shall ye be troubled, ye careless women: for the vintage shall fail, the gathering shall not come. ▼
▼ Many…: Heb. Days above a year

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Many…: Heb. Days above a year
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Many…: Heb. Days above a year

verses.text_plain: Tremble, ye women that are at ease; be troubled, ye careless ones: strip you, and make you bare, and gird sackcloth upon your loins.
verses.verse_html: 11Tremble, ye women that are at ease; be troubled, ye careless ones: strip you, and make you bare, and gird sackcloth upon your loins.

tokens.text: ye women that are at ease

verses.text_plain: They shall lament for the teats, for the pleasant fields, for the fruitful vine.
verses.verse_html:
12They shall lament for the teats, for the pleasant fields, for the fruitful vine. ▼
▼ pleasant…: Heb. fields of desire

footnotes.body_html: ▼ pleasant…: Heb. fields of desire

verses.text_plain: Upon the land of my people shall come up thorns and briers; yea, upon all the houses of joy in the joyous city:
verses.verse_html:
13Upon the land of my people shall come up thorns and briers; yea, upon all the houses of joy in the joyous city: ▼
▼ yea…: or, burning upon

footnotes.body_html: ▼ yea…: or, burning upon

verses.text_plain: Because the palaces shall be forsaken; the multitude of the city shall be left; the forts and towers shall be for dens for ever, a joy of wild asses, a pasture of flocks;
verses.verse_html:
14Because the palaces shall be forsaken; the multitude of the city shall be left; the forts and towers shall be for dens for ever, a joy of wild asses, a pasture of flocks; ▼
▼ forts…: or, clifts and watchtowers

footnotes.body_html: ▼ forts…: or, clifts and watchtowers

verses.text_plain: Until the spirit be poured upon us from on high, and the wilderness be a fruitful field, and the fruitful field be counted for a forest.
verses.verse_html: 15Until the spirit be poured upon us from on high, and the wilderness be a fruitful field, and the fruitful field be counted for a forest.

verses.text_plain: Then judgment shall dwell in the wilderness, and righteousness remain in the fruitful field.
verses.verse_html: 16Then judgment shall dwell in the wilderness, and righteousness remain in the fruitful field.

verses.text_plain: And the work of righteousness shall be peace; and the effect of righteousness quietness and assurance for ever.
verses.verse_html: 17And the work of righteousness shall be peace; and the effect of righteousness quietness and assurance for ever.

verses.text_plain: And my people shall dwell in a peaceable habitation, and in sure dwellings, and in quiet resting places;
verses.verse_html: 18And my people shall dwell in a peaceable habitation, and in sure dwellings, and in quiet resting places;

verses.text_plain: When it shall hail, coming down on the forest; and the city shall be low in a low place.
verses.verse_html:
19When it shall hail, coming down on the forest; and the city shall be low in a low place. ▼
▼ low in…: or, utterly abased

footnotes.body_html: ▼ low in…: or, utterly abased

verses.text_plain: Blessed are ye that sow beside all waters, that send forth thither the feet of the ox and the ass.
verses.verse_html: 20Blessed are ye that sow beside all waters, that send forth thither the feet of the ox and the ass.
